{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778556368151,"sessionID":"ses_1e5d0a3caffeWErV7NjHMTpxxH","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-aa631a4b39cd7818","state":{"status":"error","input":{"command":"Plan the creation of a new term 'medial prefrontal cortex'","prompt":"Plan the creation of a new UBERON term 'medial prefrontal cortex'.\n- Preferred label: medial prefrontal cortex\n- Definition: The medial prefrontal cortex (mPFC) is a subdivision of the prefrontal cortex composed of BA12, BA25, and anterior cingulate cortex: BA32, BA33, BA24. Within this region is the dorsal nexus, which interconnects multiple brain networks and plays a role in maintenance and manipulation of information (working memory), as well as supporting the control of cognitive functions such as emotion processing and regulation, memory, decision making, and conflict resolution.\n- Reference: modified from wikipedia\n- Parents: part_of 'prefrontal cortex' (UBERON:0000451), is_a 'regional part of brain' (UBERON:0002616)\n- Contributors: Michelle Giglio (https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7628-5565), Dana Gabuzda (https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4964-5083)\n\nPlease provide a detailed plan including the sequence of agents and validation steps.","subagent_type":"general"},"error":"The task tool was called with invalid arguments: SchemaError(Missing key\n  at [\"description\"]).\nPlease rewrite the input so it satisfies the expected schema.","time":{"start":1778556368146,"end":1778556368150}},"id":"prt_e1a37afa5001dYxKrpPGbKEcbL","sessionID":"ses_1e5d0a3caffeWErV7NjHMTpxxH","messageID":"msg_e1a348cf8001po2UqFmg2udI5D"}}
